Reasoning: The paper focuses on the evolution of popular websites over a period of 18 years, which falls under the domain of Web Science. Therefore, cs.WEB is the most likely sub-category. The study also involves analyzing large amounts of data, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also discusses the growth and age of websites, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper also touches upon the data set provided by the Internet Archive, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
